{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-21T17:15:57.506Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Partial derivatives"}, {"type": "text", "text": " measure how a function with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "multiple inputs"}, {"type": "text", "text": " changes when you adjust "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "one specific input"}, {"type": "text", "text": " while keeping all others fixed. They are the fundamental building blocks of gradients in machine learning, telling models exactly which parameter to tweak and by how much to reduce error."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Partial Derivatives â€” concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is â€” Clear definition and intuition"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mathematical definition:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For a function "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "f(x, y)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " with multiple variables, the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "partial derivative with respect to x"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "âˆ‚f/âˆ‚x = lim(hâ†’0) [f(x+h, y) - f(x, y)] / h"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Key notation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": The symbol "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "âˆ‚"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (called \"del\" or \"partial\") distinguishes partial derivatives from regular single-variable derivatives."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Conceptual meaning:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When a function has multiple inputs, a regular derivative is not enough.\nYou need to know how the output changes when you adjust ONE input while keeping all others fixed.\nThis is a partial derivative [web:161]."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Simple rule"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Treat all other variables as constants"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and differentiate normally."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Geometric interpretation:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For f(x, y), the partial derivative âˆ‚f/âˆ‚x at a point is the SLOPE of the surface in the x-direction.\n\nIt's what you get if you \"slice\" the 3D surface with a plane parallel to the x-axis [web:161]:\n\n       z\n       |\n       |     / â†گ Surface z = f(x, y)\n       |    /\n       |___/______ x\n      /\n     y\n\nâˆ‚f/âˆ‚x: Move only in x (y stays fixed) â†’ slope in x-direction\nâˆ‚f/âˆ‚y: Move only in y (x stays fixed) â†’ slope in y-direction"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Analogy"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Standing on a hill, if you only move east (x-direction) while staying at the same latitude (y fixed), the slope you feel is âˆ‚f/âˆ‚x."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why it matters â€” Importance in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Partial derivatives are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "essential for optimizing ML models"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ML Application"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How partial derivatives apply"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient Descent"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Each partial âˆ‚L/âˆ‚wلµ¢ tells how loss changes when weight wلµ¢ changes"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Backpropagation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Compute partial derivatives layer-by-layer through neural network"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Feature Selection"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "âˆ‚output/âˆ‚feature measures feature importance"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Hyperparameter Optimization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "âˆ‚validation_loss/âˆ‚hyperparameter guides tuning"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Regularization"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Partial derivatives of penalty terms (L1/L2)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Real example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": In training a neural network with 1 million weights, each partial derivative âˆ‚Loss/âˆ‚wلµ¢ answers: \"If I increase this one weight by a tiny amount while keeping everything else the same, does the loss go up or down, and by how much?\""}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefits â€” Key advantages"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "âœ… "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Isolate sensitivity"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Measure how sensitive output is to ONE parameter"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "âœ… "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Multi-variable optimization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Handle functions with many inputs"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "âœ… "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient construction"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Build gradient vector from partial derivatives"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "âœ… "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Efficient updates"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Know exactly which parameter to change"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs â€” Downsides and limitations"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-off"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Impact"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Only local"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Partial derivatives measure change at one point only"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Assumes independence"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Treats other variables as constant (may not reflect reality)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Computational cost"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Computing all partials for millions of parameters is expensive"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Non-differentiable points"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Some functions have undefined partial derivatives"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How it works â€” Step-by-step computation"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Rule 1: Treat other variables as constants"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "f(x, y) = xآ² + xy + yآ³\n\n# Partial derivative w.r.t. x (hold y constant):\nâˆ‚f/âˆ‚x = 2x + y + 0  = 2x + y\n#   â†‘    â†‘    â†‘\n#   xآ²   xy   yآ³ (treat as constant â†’ derivative = 0)\n\n# Partial derivative w.r.t. y (hold x constant):\nâˆ‚f/âˆ‚y = 0 + x + 3yآ² = x + 3yآ²\n#       â†‘    â†‘     â†‘\n#      xآ²   xy    yآ³"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why it works"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": When y is constant, the derivative of yآ³ is 0 (like derivative of constant 5 is 0)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example 1: Simple polynomial"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "f(x, y) = 3xآ² + 2y\n\nâˆ‚f/âˆ‚x = 6x  (derivative of 3xآ², treat 2y as constant â†’ 0)\nâˆ‚f/âˆ‚y = 2   (derivative of 2y, treat 3xآ² as constant â†’ 0)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example 2: Neural network loss"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Loss: L(w1, w2) = (w1*x1 + w2*x2 - y)آ²\n# where x1, x2, y are fixed inputs/target\n\n# Partial w.r.t. w1:\nâˆ‚L/âˆ‚w1 = 2(w1*x1 + w2*x2 - y) أ— x1\n#         â†‘ prediction error       â†‘ chain rule (derivative of inner)\n\n# Partial w.r.t. w2:\nâˆ‚L/âˆ‚w2 = 2(w1*x1 + w2*x2 - y) أ— x2"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example 3: Complex function"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "f(x, y, z) = xآ²y + sin(z) + xyz\n\n# Partial w.r.t. x:\nâˆ‚f/âˆ‚x = 2xy + 0 + yz = 2xy + yz\n#       â†‘    â†‘   â†‘\n#      xآ²y  sin(z) xyz\n\n# Partial w.r.t. y:\nâˆ‚f/âˆ‚y = xآ² + 0 + xz = xآ² + xz\n\n# Partial w.r.t. z:\nâˆ‚f/âˆ‚z = 0 + cos(z) + xy = cos(z) + xy"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Python implementations"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "SymPy (symbolic):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import sympy as sp\n\nx, y, z = sp.symbols('x y z')\nf = x**2 + x*y + y**3\n\n# Partial derivatives\ndf_dx = sp.diff(f, x)  # 2*x + y\ndf_dy = sp.diff(f, y)  # x + 3*y**2\n\nprint(f\"âˆ‚f/âˆ‚x = {df_dx}\")\nprint(f\"âˆ‚f/âˆ‚y = {df_dy}\")"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "NumPy (numerical approximation):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\ndef f(x, y):\n    return x**2 + x*y + y**3\n\n# Partial derivative w.r.t. x at point (1, 2)\nh = 1e-5\ndf_dx = (f(1 + h, 2) - f(1, 2)) / h  # â‰ˆ 4\n\n# Partial derivative w.r.t. y at point (1, 2)\ndf_dy = (f(1, 2 + h) - f(1, 2)) / h  # â‰ˆ 13\n\nprint(f\"âˆ‚f/âˆ‚x â‰ˆ {df_dx}\")  # â‰ˆ 4 (exact: 2x + y = 2أ—1 + 2 = 4)\nprint(f\"âˆ‚f/âˆ‚y â‰ˆ {df_dy}\")  # â‰ˆ 13 (exact: x + 3yآ² = 1 + 3أ—4 = 13)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "PyTorch (autograd):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\n\nx = torch.tensor(1.0, requires_grad=True)\ny = torch.tensor(2.0, requires_grad=True)\n\nz = x**2 + x*y + y**3\n\n# Compute gradients\nz.backward()\n\nprint(f\"âˆ‚z/âˆ‚x = {x.grad}\")  # 4.0\nprint(f\"âˆ‚z/âˆ‚y = {y.grad}\")  # 13.0"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key relationships â€” Connecting concepts"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Partial derivative â†’ Gradient:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "âˆ‡f = (âˆ‚f/âˆ‚x, âˆ‚f/âˆ‚y, âˆ‚f/âˆ‚z, ...)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "The gradient is just a vector of all partial derivatives"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In ML:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gradient of loss L w.r.t. weights w:\nâˆ‡L = (âˆ‚L/âˆ‚wâ‚پ, âˆ‚L/âˆ‚wâ‚‚, âˆ‚L/âˆ‚wâ‚ƒ, ..., âˆ‚L/âˆ‚wâ‚™)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Each partial derivative tells the model: \"How does loss change if I tweak THIS weight while keeping all others fixed?\""}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Chain rule with partial derivatives:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For f(g(x, y), h(x, y)):\nâˆ‚f/âˆ‚x = âˆ‚f/âˆ‚g أ— âˆ‚g/âˆ‚x + âˆ‚f/âˆ‚h أ— âˆ‚h/âˆ‚x  (multivariable chain rule)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "In backpropagation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "âˆ‚Loss/âˆ‚w = âˆ‚Loss/âˆ‚output أ— âˆ‚output/âˆ‚activation أ— âˆ‚activation/âˆ‚w"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "When to use it â€” Scenarios and decision criteria"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use partial derivatives when:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "âœ… "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Multi-parameter function"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Loss function with many weights"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "âœ… "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient computation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Need to build gradient vector"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "âœ… "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sensitivity analysis"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Measure parameter importance"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "âœ… "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Optimization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Minimize loss via gradient descent"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use regular derivative when:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "â‌Œ "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Single variable"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Function has only one input (f(x))"}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common mistakes â€” Pitfalls to avoid"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mistake"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Correction"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Not treating others as constant"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Always hold other variables fixed when computing âˆ‚f/âˆ‚x"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Confusing with total derivative"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Partial = one variable changes; Total = all variables can change"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Ignoring chain rule"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use chain rule for composed functions (backpropagation)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Manual computation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use autograd (PyTorch/TensorFlow) for neural networks"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best practices â€” Proven approaches"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. Use autograd frameworks"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import torch\n\nx = torch.tensor([1.0, 2.0, 3.0], requires_grad=True)\ny = x**2 + 3*x  # Multi-parameter function\ny.backward()\n\nprint(f\"Gradients: {x.grad}\")  # [2, 5, 8] = all partials"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. Compute all partials for gradient"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Gradient = vector of all partial derivatives\ngradient = np.array([grad_w1, grad_w2, grad_w3, ...])"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. Visualize with 3D plots"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Plot f(x, y) surface to see partial derivatives as slopes\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Partial derivative = sensitivity to ONE variable"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": âˆ‚f/âˆ‚x measures change when x varies, y fixed"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Treat others as constants"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Hold all other variables fixed"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Symbol âˆ‚"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Called \"del\" or \"partial,\" distinguishes from regular derivative d"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Geometric meaning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Slope of surface in one direction (slice parallel to axis)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Gradient = vector of partials"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": âˆ‡f = (âˆ‚f/âˆ‚x, âˆ‚f/âˆ‚y,...)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "In ML"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Each âˆ‚L/âˆ‚wلµ¢ answers: \"How does loss change if I tweak weight wلµ¢ while keeping others same?\""}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Chain rule"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Used in backpropagation for composed functions"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Essential for optimization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Gradient descent uses partials to update weights"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Feature importance"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": âˆ‚output/âˆ‚feature measures sensitivity"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use autograd"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": PyTorch computes all partials automatically"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For Generative AI, partial derivatives are the building blocks of everything: each weight update in training, each backpropagation step, and each optimization algorithm relies on computing partial derivatives to determine precisely how each parameter affects the loss."}]}]}}